$$ \varepsilon = \frac{{\left( {R_{\max } - R_{\min } } \right)}} {{2R_{{\text{mean}}} }} $$\end{document} where R is the radius of curvature of the LAD. The present study used a deformation parameter of 0.6 which falls within the physiological range of LAD deformations.15 A sinusoidal function as given below was used to specify the time dependent variation of curvature of the LAD (Fig. 2) 3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
