$$ R\left( t \right) = R_{{\text{mean}}} \left[ {1 + \varepsilon \cdot \cos (\omega t)} \right] $$\end{document} where ω is the angular frequency of deformation. A user-defined function was written to apply this curvature waveform as a grid motion boundary condition. The tube inlet was fixed constant in the simulations at all times. This allowed the centre of curvature to vary sinusoidally in a cardiac cycle.

The mass transport of species in the arterial lumen is mathematically described using the three dimensional convection-diffusion equation 4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
